How this component is used in Tab Audio Recorder
------------------------------------------------

lamejs is used only as an optional, in-browser encoder: when the user chooses
"MP3" as the export format, the already-recorded tab audio is re-encoded to MP3
locally inside the extension's offscreen document. The library is bundled and
loaded locally; it makes no network requests and requires no extra permissions.

Because lame.min.js is shipped as a separate, unmodified file, it can be
replaced with another build of lamejs of the same version, satisfying the
LGPL-3.0 relinking provision.
